# Lovable & Vite Constraints

This project uses `@lovable.dev/vite-tanstack-config`. Misconfigured Vite breaks **both** Lovable preview and Cursor local dev.

## Do not

- Add these plugins manually (already included — duplicates break the app):
  `tanstackStart`, `viteReact`, `tailwindcss`, `tsConfigPaths`, `nitro`, `componentTagger`, path alias, dedupe plugins
- Replace `defineConfig` import with plain `vite` config
- Change SSR entry away from `src/server.ts` without updating `tanstackStart.server.entry`
- Remove error handling in `server.ts` / `start.ts` without replacement
- Upgrade major Vite/TanStack/Lovable packages casually — ask user first

## Safe changes

- Pass extra options via `defineConfig({ vite: { ... } })` only when needed
- Edit `src/server.ts` for SSR error normalization — keep `fetch` export default

## package.json scripts

Keep standard: `dev`, `build`, `lint`, `format`. Do not rename without updating README and AGENTS.md.

## If build fails after your edit

Revert config changes first, then fix application code.
